# Coding Standards

Source: `Plans/15-coding-standards.md`

## Language

- TypeScript **strict** + `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`. No `any` — use `unknown` and narrow.
- ESM only. React 18 function components + hooks. Fastify plugins are async.
- Explicit parameter and return types on every function.
- Shared types in `packages/types`. Zod is source of truth; types via `z.infer<>`.
- Enums: `as const` + Zod enum — avoid TS `enum`.

## Naming & layout

- Files: `kebab-case`. React components: `PascalCase.tsx`.
- Feature-folder modules (see `03-backend-api.md`). No catch-all `utils/` bins.
- Booleans affirmative: `isReady`, not `notReady`.

## Money & weight (hard)

```ts
// ❌ BAD
const total = price * qty

// ✅ GOOD — Decimal.js in packages/domain only
const total = new Decimal(price).mul(qty).toFixed(2) // string on wire
```

- DB: money `NUMERIC(14,2)`, weight `NUMERIC(10,3)`
- Wire: money as **string** (`"51240.00"`)
- Formatters only in `packages/ui`

## Errors

API: `{ code, message, details, requestId }`. Never leak Postgres/Supabase internals. Toast user-friendly messages; Sentry gets full detail.

## Testing

- Vitest unit/integration · Playwright E2E (happy path + offline write path)
- `packages/domain` ≥ 95% · API modules ≥ 85%
- Every new tenant table: RLS leak test with second tenant
- Fixtures in adjacent `__fixtures__/`

## Definition of Done (feature)

Zod in `packages/types` · domain logic + tests · API + integration test · loading/empty/error UI · 375px responsive · keyboard + `aria-label` · offline write path (or documented online-only) · idempotent (`client_uuid` / Idempotency-Key) · RLS leak test · Sentry boundary · plan MD updated · Playwright happy path

## Git

Branches: `feature/<slug>`, `fix/<slug>`. Conventional commits. PR ≤ 400 lines (else ADR). Human merges; agents propose only.
